    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.4" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Star Rte 2 Bx84
                        Avenal, Calif.
                        April 15 - 1959
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Recieved your letter promising to autograph one of your books &#8212; "When the Tree Flowered" &#8212; so I sent for a new copy for this special favor. I like the book so much and will certainly appreciate anything you care to write in it.</p>
                
                <p>I'm going along quite well on a 2nd Dakota book -- Naturally we are happy about the kindness and good sale given "Dakota Cowboy" &#8212; and especially the "send off" <hi rend="underline">Chicago Westerners</hi> gave it recently, after the contest concerning the best of "Best Books of the West 1958". In a letter from them, they say "Dakota Cowboy" was <add>the only book</add> on <hi rend="underline">every</hi> list submitted to them <del/><add>a</add>nd on every other list they consullted &#8212; some where &#8212; top to bottom &#8212; it was there. That is something to be truly grateful for.</p>
                
                <p>I wish I could meet you some day. You must be a wonderful man.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely &#8212;</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Ike Blasingame</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
